cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes a marker-less and dynamic tracking concept using simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) of the operating theater environment, which involves computer vision techniques. 
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the use of augmented reality (AR) to provide in situ visualization of medical data directly at the surgical site, which involves human-computer interaction. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper involves the visualization of 3D medical data using optical see-through head mounted displays, which involves graphics techniques. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses the use of tracking and visualization technologies to assist orthopedic surgeons in navigating surgical tools percutaneously, which involves robotics techniques. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves the use of multimedia technologies such as optical see-through head mounted displays to provide in situ visualization of medical data.
